				The only real use I've found for Barkspur in a group setting is when all three of these conditions are present: 1) I'm main healer, <u><i>and</i></u> 2) the group is low on dps, <u><i>and</i></u> 3) every mob 'enrages' (e.g. ashengate). In such a scenario, stacking the extra DS helps compensate for the tank turning off attack during the last tick or two of combat.<br><br>Otherwise the spell is lackluster -- which means, 99.9% of the time. Honestly, if any of those 3 conditions isn't true, the spell isn't worth keeping memmed. I.E. If I'm not the main healer, I can nuke; if we have plenty of dps in the group, the tank's doesn't matter as much; and if the mobs don't enrage, there's no added urgency to get the mob dead when it gets low health.<br><br>I would much rather have a .5 second nuke similar to Sting of the Queen. Now that spell is a nice quick way to get past an enraging mob ... and what's funny is how, despite how much some shaman have tried to downplay that spell, *every* shaman I've grouped with has already made it a habit of casting every time it pops, quite easily between their other spells. <br><br>Regards,<br><br>Mahzz<br><div></div>
				
