				There is desireability to be appreciated in attack debuffs, its just
not helpful that people are rather ignorant about it because the effect
isn't as noticeably visible as a mob hitting fewer times / minute, and
when they do get used those people probably end up thinking "oh that
tank, hes got uber mitigation taking such low damage most of the time"
when really it was mostly the debuffs.<br>
<br>
I play a druid at times with my cleric tanking, I sometimes play a
shaman instead (druid moreso) and I can weigh the options of Slow vs
Attack debuffs just from watching parses, or just the mob rounds
enacted upon me. There's no xp zone that I can't duo with either now,
and whilst slow is obviously best in Ashengate (fire immunity 4tlose),
FC is harsher deeper in than AG by a significant amount- slowed they
can still hurt from spikes but at least its at a lesser rate, unslowed
with debuffs they can hurt but at least the healing is more predictable
with significantly fewer spikes. Which is better? /shrug, I haven't
parsed in that case, but the fact is I manage with either. <br>
<br>
Now its an extreme example yes, but consider the dps of just a cleric
and druid, and just a cleric and shaman. Its pretty low. Now consider a
group managing there... and yes, I would do groups without slowers with
a druid, and yes I would do groups with just a slower, but also I love
groups where slow and attack debuffs are both present- it makes
multipulls much more manageable. <br>
<br>
If I could, I would 3 box and have a druid AND shaman- that would be the real holy trinity <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-very-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br>
<br>
Anyways, I'm not thinking the caster buff is a bad idea- I think it
nice, but I have to disagree with statements saying druids aren't
desireable. Its there and you are a desired class very highly by people
who understand the benefits- even if they are decked out in the best
gear (might be thought oh, with high AC attack debuffs aren't worth it.
I still have groups with Igneous and druids still cast attack debuffs,
can't get better than the highest ac warrior, and I still see
benefits), the rest of EQ just needs to stop being stupid and ignorant.<br>
